01:10.470 --> 01:11.837
-child:
<i> The old people said</i>

01:11.839 --> 01:14.573
<i> that sadness creates</i>
<i> a hole in our hearts...</i>

01:14.575 --> 01:19.244
<i> And that the spirit of</i>
<i> shapishico with fill it.</i>

01:22.849 --> 01:26.552
<i> At first, the spirit</i>
<i> goes unnoticed...</i>

01:26.554 --> 01:28.687
<i> Hiding behind our eyes...</i>

01:28.689 --> 01:30.589
<i> But in the dark...</i>

01:31.458 --> 01:33.826
<i> It grows stronger.</i>

01:35.095 --> 01:39.264
<i> Shapishico.</i>

01:53.813 --> 01:56.315
-Child:
<i> It drives us into madness...</i>

01:56.317 --> 02:00.586
<i> Whispering in our ears</i>
<i>until we sacrifice ourselves...</i>

02:00.588 --> 02:02.855
<i> To set the spirit free.</i>

02:05.793 --> 02:09.360
<i> Shapishico.</i>

02:26.679 --> 02:28.580
-Child:
<i> And it spreads...</i>

02:28.582 --> 02:30.616
<i> Like a sickness.</i>

02:30.750 --> 02:33.519
<i> The old people tell us</i>
<i> these stories...</i>

02:33.521 --> 02:35.521
<i> But they forget...</i>

02:36.356 --> 02:39.758
<i> That these stories are true.</i>

03:33.813 --> 03:36.315
-Hello, sir...
-How is it going, man?

03:36.317 --> 03:37.216
-Michael.

03:37.218 --> 03:38.984
I was here last night and...

03:38.986 --> 03:41.353
I left my cell phone.

03:41.355 --> 03:42.421
-Last night?

03:42.423 --> 03:43.789
-Do you have a...

03:43.791 --> 03:44.856
Lost and found?

03:44.858 --> 03:46.625
-Lost and found?

03:46.627 --> 03:48.260
-Yes.

03:48.761 --> 03:50.262
Yes.

03:51.331 --> 03:53.765
Yes! This one.

03:54.367 --> 03:56.468
-Are you sure?

03:56.970 --> 03:58.270
-Yes!

04:01.709 --> 04:03.709
I have to call my girlfriend...

04:03.711 --> 04:06.979
Otherwise, I'm fucked.
You know what I mean?

04:09.249 --> 04:10.849
Thank you.

04:11.584 --> 04:14.519
You're the best. The best.

04:27.934 --> 04:29.501
-Hi, Hector.

04:29.503 --> 04:31.370
-Hello, Michael.

04:31.771 --> 04:34.539
-You have a very
generous grandmother.

04:34.541 --> 04:38.310
The same type of gift
over and over?

04:38.312 --> 04:39.978
-She has Alzheimer's.

04:39.980 --> 04:41.413
-If you need money...

04:41.415 --> 04:43.782
I could help you find work.

04:43.784 --> 04:45.717
It could be easier than...

04:45.719 --> 04:47.653
Whatever you call this.

04:47.655 --> 04:49.454
-Resourcefulness.

04:49.456 --> 04:52.557
Besides I'm not really
looking for a job.

04:52.825 --> 04:56.295
I'm actually surprised you even
sell cell phones in here.

04:56.297 --> 04:58.697
-Cell phones pay the bills...

04:58.699 --> 05:02.434
Everything else
here is like a hobby.

05:02.802 --> 05:03.969
-Strange hobby.

05:03.971 --> 05:06.038
-I love history.

05:06.040 --> 05:07.839
It's always changing.

05:07.841 --> 05:09.007
New discoveries...

05:09.009 --> 05:10.742
Truth brought to light.

05:10.744 --> 05:16.081
Tomorrow everything
we know about the past
could be different.

05:19.085 --> 05:20.619
-Not everything.

05:20.621 --> 05:21.920
Bye, Hector.

05:21.922 --> 05:23.655
-Good luck.

05:38.439 --> 05:41.973
-Out! Out! Get the hell
out my driveway!

05:41.975 --> 05:42.874
Out!

05:42.876 --> 05:43.775
Out!

05:43.777 --> 05:44.843
Out!

05:45.345 --> 05:46.578
-I'm sorry.

06:46.440 --> 06:48.507
-Michael:
Danny?

06:56.149 --> 06:57.449
Danny.

06:57.850 --> 06:58.183
Danny!

07:09.830 --> 07:10.929
-Fuck!

07:10.931 --> 07:11.930
-Sir...

07:11.932 --> 07:13.765
-Fuck, man!
-I'm sorry!

07:13.767 --> 07:15.200
Sir... I'm so sorry!

07:15.202 --> 07:16.201
-Asshole!
-I'm sorry!

07:16.203 --> 07:17.536
-What? Get out.
-I'm sorry!

07:17.538 --> 07:20.439
-What are you doing in there?
Get out of my car!

07:20.441 --> 07:21.840
You little cunt!
-Sir.

07:21.842 --> 07:23.208
-Fuck!
-Sir...

07:24.812 --> 07:26.978
-What the hell is going on?
Leave him alone!

07:26.980 --> 07:27.712
-Mind your own business!

07:27.714 --> 07:32.050
-When the cops get here,
I'll tell them you
almost killed this guy.

07:32.052 --> 07:33.819
-Get out of here.
-You get out!

07:33.821 --> 07:38.857
-I'm watching you, fucker!
-Get the hell out!

07:39.459 --> 07:41.626
-What a couple of idiots.

07:41.794 --> 07:43.862
-You'll get what you deserve!

07:48.701 --> 07:49.768
-Are you okay?

07:49.770 --> 07:51.203
-I'm okay, I should be fine.

07:51.205 --> 07:52.804
-So what was that all about?

07:52.806 --> 07:55.140
-Well... apparently,
that guy is not a big fan

07:55.142 --> 07:57.509
of people sleeping in
the back seat of his car.

07:57.511 --> 07:59.544
-So you're homeless?

07:59.546 --> 08:01.947
-I prefer the term traveler.

08:01.949 --> 08:05.650
It seems less...

08:05.652 --> 08:06.952
-Pathetic?

08:06.954 --> 08:08.720
-Yeah.

08:08.722 --> 08:08.987
I guess.

08:08.989 --> 08:12.924
I left home with enough
money to last me a year
and I've been gone for two.

08:12.926 --> 08:15.126
-Why haven't you gone home?

08:15.963 --> 08:18.129
I'm not quite ready for that.

08:18.131 --> 08:20.232
Anyway, I'm Michael.

08:20.234 --> 08:21.500
Thanks for...

08:21.502 --> 08:22.834
-No, no it was cool.

08:22.836 --> 08:26.238
Look, medellin has worked
hard to leave its past behind.

08:26.240 --> 08:28.773
We don't need any dead
Americans in the street.

08:28.775 --> 08:31.943
I know some guys who have
a place outside the city...

08:31.945 --> 08:33.945
And they're having
a little party tonight.

08:33.947 --> 08:35.813
You should come,
check it out.

08:35.816 --> 08:40.552
Maybe they might be able to set
you up with a place to stay.

08:44.256 --> 08:46.124
Come by around 10!

09:41.147 --> 09:42.280
-Hello?

09:47.086 --> 09:48.086
Hello?

09:57.598 --> 09:58.830
-Hey!

10:13.713 --> 10:16.147
-I'm looking for melody.

10:21.020 --> 10:24.990
-Come in, come in!

11:10.036 --> 11:12.937
-Hey! You!

11:12.939 --> 11:15.040
Come here.

11:22.815 --> 11:23.948
How are you, my friend?

11:23.950 --> 11:25.784
-I'm Michael.

11:28.187 --> 11:29.688
-Michael?

11:30.189 --> 11:32.090
Do you know any Michael?

11:32.725 --> 11:34.426
Pauly, you know any Michael?

11:34.428 --> 11:35.060
-No!

11:35.062 --> 11:37.262
-Melody invited me.

11:37.264 --> 11:38.163
-Melody?

11:40.400 --> 11:43.234
-Melody?

11:43.236 --> 11:44.803
Nope.

11:44.805 --> 11:46.304
Don't know any melody.

11:46.306 --> 11:48.339
-Pauly:
Nope!

11:49.875 --> 11:52.110
-It's my bad, sorry guys.

11:53.947 --> 11:55.146
-No wait!

11:55.148 --> 11:56.047
Hey!

11:56.049 --> 11:57.115
Hey!

11:57.349 --> 11:58.917
It's all right, okay?

11:58.919 --> 12:00.251
No, stay come on.

12:00.253 --> 12:02.721
See, we are having a party...

12:02.723 --> 12:04.422
And you're here...

12:04.424 --> 12:05.724
So...

12:06.826 --> 12:07.859
Have a seat...

12:07.861 --> 12:09.461
Take a load off.

12:12.064 --> 12:13.198
Sit down!

12:15.901 --> 12:17.035
Sit down!

12:18.270 --> 12:20.271
Where are you from, Michael?

12:23.075 --> 12:24.375
-San Diego.

12:24.377 --> 12:26.010
-San Diego?

12:26.512 --> 12:29.180
You are a long way from home.

12:31.383 --> 12:34.018
Excuse me, I forgot my manners.

12:34.020 --> 12:35.019
You need a drink.

12:35.021 --> 12:38.923
And you, Vinnie,
you've had too much...

12:38.925 --> 12:40.291
As always.

12:40.293 --> 12:41.392
Here.

12:42.895 --> 12:44.129
-I'm good.

12:46.465 --> 12:47.799
-I'm offering you a drink.

12:47.801 --> 12:51.770
It's disrespectful
to turn it down.

13:01.414 --> 13:02.781
-Manuela!

13:06.352 --> 13:07.485
-Michael.

13:10.856 --> 13:12.924
Do you know the sound...

13:13.092 --> 13:15.293
A dead American makes...

13:16.195 --> 13:18.062
In medellin?

13:22.868 --> 13:24.335
You hear it?

13:24.970 --> 13:26.337
That's it.

13:27.873 --> 13:28.973
Nothing.

13:29.909 --> 13:31.176
-Melody:
Jacob!

13:32.945 --> 13:33.511
-Melody!

13:33.513 --> 13:34.112
-Playing nice?

13:34.114 --> 13:36.381
-Oh, my Princess, yes,
yes, we are playing nice.

13:36.383 --> 13:41.519
You know, a little scare,
just makes a boy into a man.

13:42.488 --> 13:44.322
Right, Michael?

13:44.324 --> 13:45.890
-Yeah.

13:46.258 --> 13:48.459
We were just getting
to know each other.

13:48.461 --> 13:48.927
-Yes!

13:48.929 --> 13:53.364
That is right. We are just
getting to know each other.

13:53.366 --> 13:54.599
Nothing more.

13:58.103 --> 14:00.071
To old friends...

14:03.275 --> 14:04.876
And to new.

14:05.911 --> 14:11.216
Welcome to the house
of the dead men.

14:14.286 --> 14:14.853
-This...

14:14.855 --> 14:17.488
This is the start
of a good relationship.

14:18.457 --> 14:19.557
I think.

14:20.025 --> 14:21.392
Manuela!

14:22.027 --> 14:24.195
The music!

15:14.213 --> 15:15.380
-Hello there.

15:15.382 --> 15:17.515
How are you feeling?

15:18.284 --> 15:19.617
-Like shit.

15:24.590 --> 15:25.924
What happened?

15:25.926 --> 15:27.592
-See for yourself.

15:27.594 --> 15:31.162
The night wasn't all bad.

15:32.564 --> 15:33.464
Do you like it?

15:33.466 --> 15:36.434
-Yeah, good picture.

15:36.635 --> 15:39.070
-Hey so, who's Danny?

15:39.438 --> 15:43.641
Yeah, you were saying
his name last night.

15:47.346 --> 15:49.314
-He's my baby brother.

15:51.517 --> 15:53.117
He died.

15:55.554 --> 15:57.188
-I'm sorry.

16:03.095 --> 16:05.263
-Good, you're awake.

16:06.632 --> 16:09.434
Come on, let me show you around.

16:09.601 --> 16:10.735
-I have to go anyway.

16:10.737 --> 16:12.403
-Are you sure?
-Yeah.

16:12.405 --> 16:13.237
You have fun.

16:13.239 --> 16:15.139
-Are you sure?
-Yeah.

16:15.141 --> 16:16.975
Behave yourself.

16:17.743 --> 16:19.377
-Always.

16:19.979 --> 16:22.013
She's a good girl.

16:26.251 --> 16:27.485
Come on.

16:34.493 --> 16:37.195
Jacob:
Out here, nobody fucks with us.

16:37.197 --> 16:39.130
We are completely off the grid.

16:39.132 --> 16:40.031
-Michael:
What was this place?

16:40.033 --> 16:43.634
-Jacob:
It was a psychiatric
hospital for women.

16:44.269 --> 16:47.005
Shut down 15 years ago.

16:48.240 --> 16:50.541
-Why did they close it down?

16:50.543 --> 16:54.746
-It has what I guess you
would call a "disturbing past."

17:03.389 --> 17:06.257
Down this hallway,
there was a boy...

17:07.059 --> 17:09.227
Mauricio rojas.

17:09.661 --> 17:10.795
He was born here.

17:10.797 --> 17:14.398
All the children in this
wing were born here.

17:15.134 --> 17:16.768
<i> Mauricio...</i>

17:17.603 --> 17:18.236
<i> Killed himself.</i>

17:18.238 --> 17:23.040
Drove the splintered end
of a headboard
right through his chest.

17:24.542 --> 17:25.810
-Jesus.

17:27.512 --> 17:29.113
-Later that same night,

17:29.115 --> 17:33.117
all the children in this wing
committed suicide.

17:36.488 --> 17:37.488
They slit their wrists

17:37.490 --> 17:40.391
with glass from
a broken lightbulb.

17:44.063 --> 17:45.797
No one knows why.

17:48.067 --> 17:50.101
I think the doctors...

17:50.103 --> 17:51.803
They fucked them up.

17:52.604 --> 17:54.739
They were tired of
living in these cages...

17:54.741 --> 17:58.242
So they got out
on their own terms.

17:59.578 --> 18:02.480
Let's get the fuck out of here.

18:19.465 --> 18:20.765
Welcome home.

18:20.767 --> 18:22.500
-Thanks.

19:02.208 --> 19:04.308
-Michael:
Hello?

19:44.883 --> 19:46.684
-Freedom.

19:46.919 --> 19:49.887
When I look at you,
i don't see freedom.

19:50.455 --> 19:52.456
I see slaves.

19:54.326 --> 19:56.494
Slaves to the past...

19:57.496 --> 19:58.930
To regret.

19:59.665 --> 20:03.968
The only true freedom
lies in death.

20:05.237 --> 20:06.637
And as one of the dead men...

20:06.639 --> 20:11.642
Man: Ready to die!

20:12.811 --> 20:15.313
-I can tell you...

20:15.781 --> 20:17.448
Freedom...

20:17.450 --> 20:18.950
It feels...

20:18.952 --> 20:19.984
Fucking good!

20:24.523 --> 20:25.723
-Michael...

20:26.458 --> 20:28.326
Come up here.

20:28.328 --> 20:31.262
-I'm, I'm good
where I am, thanks.

20:31.597 --> 20:33.231
-No you're not.

20:34.867 --> 20:37.602
You're living in
a fucking bubble...

20:38.003 --> 20:40.871
And it's about time it's popped.

20:41.540 --> 20:42.707
Come on.

20:49.848 --> 20:53.651
-Man:
That's it, there you go.

20:54.786 --> 20:58.689
Michael here,
he needs a place to stay.

20:59.324 --> 21:01.692
But if he wants
to be one of us...

21:01.793 --> 21:04.362
There's one more thing he needs.

21:04.596 --> 21:06.664
One foot in the grave.

21:09.334 --> 21:11.335
But first a toast...

21:13.338 --> 21:15.406
To new beginnings!

21:15.607 --> 21:21.779
Up! Down! Center! Inside!

21:30.922 --> 21:32.823
-And now...

21:33.492 --> 21:35.559
Now a real drink.

21:38.630 --> 21:39.463
-What's that?

21:39.465 --> 21:41.932
-A friend wouldn't ask.

22:00.352 --> 22:02.620
-What the fuck was that?

22:02.622 --> 22:03.754
-Oh. That...

22:03.756 --> 22:06.824
--...was just the beginning.

22:13.899 --> 22:15.933
Let's fucking party!

24:12.017 --> 24:14.618
-Bye, Michael.

24:16.121 --> 24:17.621
Danny?

24:18.590 --> 24:19.824
Danny.

25:13.678 --> 25:14.612
-Hey!

25:14.614 --> 25:15.713
Hey!

25:15.715 --> 25:16.881
Michael!

25:16.883 --> 25:18.148
Hey!

25:18.150 --> 25:19.884
Look at me.

25:20.652 --> 25:22.853
Michael, are you with me?

25:23.822 --> 25:24.922
-Yes?

25:25.524 --> 25:27.091
-You see me?

25:27.093 --> 25:28.025
-Yeah.

25:28.027 --> 25:31.562
There's someone standing
right in front of you.

25:32.197 --> 25:33.297
Look.

25:35.800 --> 25:37.668
Can you see?

25:38.870 --> 25:40.271
Yes?

25:44.709 --> 25:46.544
Michael...

25:47.112 --> 25:49.680
It's someone you hate.

25:51.249 --> 25:53.250
Someone...

25:54.052 --> 25:56.720
You want to see dead.

25:58.723 --> 26:00.057
Hey.

26:00.059 --> 26:01.759
Look.

26:12.170 --> 26:13.804
Do it.

26:30.355 --> 26:32.690
Michael... Michael!

26:33.258 --> 26:35.359
You with me? Yes?

26:37.629 --> 26:39.129
Hush.

26:42.734 --> 26:43.133
Congratulations,

26:43.135 --> 26:47.037
you just took your first step
to becoming a dead man.

27:04.255 --> 27:06.690
-Michael:
So what the hell did
you give me last night?

27:06.692 --> 27:09.259
-Blackstar.
It's similar to yagé.

27:09.261 --> 27:11.996
Various vines and roots
from the jungle.

27:11.998 --> 27:14.965
Tourists call it ayahuasca.

27:14.967 --> 27:18.102
-Wait. You gave me
fucking ayahuasca?

27:18.737 --> 27:21.038
-It helps you open your
mind to the spiritual world

27:21.040 --> 27:23.874
confronting your
personal demons.

27:24.175 --> 27:26.777
Today, it is used in
healing ceremonies.

27:27.345 --> 27:27.978
Shit like that.

27:27.980 --> 27:31.815
Still... a little heads-up
would've been nice.

27:31.916 --> 27:34.284
-What would be
the fun of that?

27:39.091 --> 27:42.326
-Man:
This food is disgusting!
It has hairs on it.

27:42.328 --> 27:44.828
Do me a favor and bring
me a plate of good food.

27:44.830 --> 27:46.897
-Waitress:
Sorry, sir. They'll
make you a new one.

27:46.899 --> 27:49.366
-Of all the places in the world,
why medellin?

27:49.368 --> 27:50.934
-I was born here.

27:50.936 --> 27:51.935
My mom was Colombian.

27:51.937 --> 27:54.171
-I knew there was something
about you I liked.

27:54.173 --> 27:57.708
-She died when I was five.
I don't remember her at all.

27:57.710 --> 28:01.045
My dad was stationed
here when they met and...

28:02.013 --> 28:04.948
He didn't even know
i was born until she died.

28:04.950 --> 28:11.288
After she passed, he came down
and took me up to San Diego.

28:20.098 --> 28:21.765
-Now you're back.

28:23.301 --> 28:26.970
-How about you? You don't sound
like you are from around here.

28:26.972 --> 28:28.038
-No, I was born in this city.

28:28.040 --> 28:29.873
But I spent most of
my time traveling.

28:29.875 --> 28:32.443
Living with shamans
in Chile, Peru...

28:32.445 --> 28:34.344
Studying at ashrams in India.

28:34.346 --> 28:37.081
Learning
the intricacies of life...

28:37.083 --> 28:38.482
And death.

28:38.484 --> 28:40.084
So what made you come back?

28:40.086 --> 28:41.719
<i> "Chimba."</i>

28:41.721 --> 28:42.753
Pussy.

28:45.156 --> 28:46.223
-No.

28:48.259 --> 28:48.892
-Home.
-Yeah.

28:48.894 --> 28:51.862
-It has a way
of calling us back.

28:52.130 --> 28:53.764
Let me ask you a question.

28:53.766 --> 28:57.301
If you knew you had
one year left to live...

28:58.136 --> 29:00.971
How would you live
the rest of your life?

29:01.106 --> 29:04.141
You see, life is just a long,
scenic drive off of a cliff.

29:04.143 --> 29:06.410
Most people try to distract
themselves along the way.

29:06.412 --> 29:11.215
They turn to god or try
to live a meaningful life.

29:11.217 --> 29:12.750
But at the end of the road,

29:12.752 --> 29:14.485
whether you're a good person...

29:14.487 --> 29:15.953
Or a son of a bitch...

29:15.955 --> 29:18.155
It's all the same cliff.

29:18.523 --> 29:20.924
-So just do whatever
the hell we want?

29:20.926 --> 29:21.825
-Exactly.

29:21.827 --> 29:24.194
<i> Shapishico.</i>

29:24.496 --> 29:29.933
-Let me show you some things
your boyfriend can't. Come on!

29:30.301 --> 29:32.436
Why are you playing hard to get?

29:32.438 --> 29:33.103
Huh?

29:33.105 --> 29:37.307
-See, me and the others, we live
as if we are already dead.

29:37.309 --> 29:38.909
A dead man has
no responsibilities.

29:38.911 --> 29:39.810
He does not live
for anyone else.

29:39.812 --> 29:44.081
He doesn't worry of how
he will make a living.

29:45.150 --> 29:47.284
A dead man has no past.

29:48.186 --> 29:50.120
-A dead man has no regrets.

29:50.122 --> 29:53.423
-We do what we want,
when we want...

29:54.025 --> 29:56.026
